1.Imagine you are building an Android app in which you will need multiple UI elements consisting of the same structure. 
Which of the following is true about how you should define the composable for this UI element?
->You should define the composable once in such a way that it is reusable.

2.Which of the following does an Activity represent?
->The app screen.

3.Which of the following is true about XML documents?
->All XML documents are hierarchical.

4.What is the Activity lifecycle?
->States an activity instance goes through from start to termination

5.Which of the following are examples of view groups? Select all that apply. 
->RelativeLayout.
->FrameLayout.
->LinearLayout.

6.Which of the following is based on the declarative approach?
->Jetpack Compose.

7.Which of the following is used to tell Jetpack Compose Preview how to generate a preview of the design you are working on?
->@Preview.

8.When you are specifying the size of an element on an Android UI, you can use the dp unit of measurement. This term is shorthand for?
->Density-independent pixel.

9.Which of the following correspond to the attributes of XML elements?
->Object properties.

10.Which of the following are guides in organizing and arranging other UI elements on the screen?
->layouts.
